[[File:Bring_Us_Together.jpg|thumb]]

在美国人民之中达成和解也是汉弗莱竞选认输声明中的主题：“我已经尽了全力。我输了，尼克松先生赢了。民主进程仍然在妥善运转，所以现在让我们开始努力完成团结祖国的迫切任务吧。”<ref name="UPI 1968 in review" />

尼克松在获胜演说中提及到访德什勒的经历后，学校管理人员再次问起学生们有关标语的事，这次科尔站了出来。她表示之前没有承认是因为标语不是自己写的<ref name="Ionne 1968–11–09" />。多位记者在校长的办公室里采访了这位小女孩，科尔表示，她觉得尼克松就是一个能把国家重新团结在一起的人<ref name="Ionne 1968–11–09" />。她还表示，接受那些来自[[哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿]]、纽约和[[芝加哥|芝加哥]]的记者们采访比坐在[[历史|历史]]课上要有趣多了<ref name="Ripley 1968–11–08" />。[[托莱多_(俄亥俄州)|托莱多]]的《刀刃报》（{{lang|en|Blade}}）对事情进行了调查，但无法确定标语是谁做的，或是科尔将之丢弃后又发生了什么。村上的警察局长约翰·贝尔（{{lang|en|John Baer}}）表示：“我想这肯定是咱们这儿发生过的最重大的事情了。”<ref name="Toledo Blade 1968–11–08" />德什勒《旗帜报》（{{lang|en|Flag}}）编辑保罗·沙尔夫（{{lang|en|Paul Scharf}}）表示，标语的来源或之后的命运可能永远都是一个谜<ref name="Toledo Blade 1968–11–08" />。萨菲尔表示是摩尔告诉自己有这么一个显然是手工制作的标语脱颖而出，并且不是由当地的尼克松竞选工作人员制作的<ref name="Safire 2008" />。

早在11月7日，距德什勒不远的亨利县[[县城|县城]][[拿破仑_(俄亥俄州)|拿破仑]]的地方报纸《西北信号报》（{{lang|en|Northwest Signal}}）就报道称德什勒的商户正考虑一起凑钱送科尔去哥伦比亚特区<ref name="Northwest Signal 1968–11–08">{{citation | periodical = Northwest Signal | date = 1968-11-08 | title = Who made that sign? | place = Napoleon, Ohio | page = 4}}</ref>，次日该报发表社论，称科尔将与真正制作该标语的人一起前往华盛顿参加尼克松总统的就职典礼<ref name="Northwest Signal 1968–11–08" />。1968年11月19日，竞选特别助理，尼克松的长期顾问[[默里·乔蒂纳|默里·乔蒂纳]]提议邀请科尔一家人前来参加就职典礼，并且让科尔坐到主题彩车上<ref name="Chotiner 1968–11–19">{{citation | last = Chotiner | first = Murray | date = 1968-11-19 | title = Memo from Murray Chotiner to H.R. Haldeman and John Mitchell (November 19, 1968) in Box 19, Folder 1 (Virtual Library) | work = Nixon Presidential Returned Materials Collection: White House Special Files (WHSF) | publisher = Richard Nixon Presidential Library and Museum | archivedate = 2012-09-23 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120923220154/http://www.nixonlibrary.gov/virtuallibrary/documents/whsfreturned/WHSF_Box_19/WHSF19-01.pdf | url = http://www.nixonlibrary.gov/virtuallibrary/documents/whsfreturned/WHSF_Box_19/WHSF19-01.pdf | format = PDF | accessdate = 2013-11-28 }}</ref>。尼克松随后邀请了科尔的父母及其家人出席就职典礼<ref name="NYTimes 1968–12–04">{{citation | periodical = The New York Times | date = 1968-12-04 | title = Ohio girl who held up sign invited to capital by Nixon | url = http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=FB0715FD355C147493C6A91789D95F4C8685F9 | accessdate = 2013-11-28 | archivedate = 2012-11-06 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121106062404/http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=FB0715FD355C147493C6A91789D95F4C8685F9 }}{{subscription required}}</ref>，这家人由就职典礼委员会带到哥伦比亚特区<ref name="NYTimes 1969–01–19">{{citation | periodical = The New York Times | date = 1969-01-19 | title = Washington awaits the inauguration | url = http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F60715F73E5D137A93CBA8178AD85F4D8685F9 | accessdate = 2013-11-28 | archivedate = 2012-11-06 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121106062439/http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F60715F73E5D137A93CBA8178AD85F4D8685F9 }}{{subscription required}}</ref>。维奇·琳恩·科尔带着一个重新制作的标语牌登上了就职典礼游行的主题彩车<ref name="Time 1969–01–17">{{citation |periodical=Time |date=1969-01-17 |title=Toward the Nixon inauguration |url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,838850,00.html |accessdate=2013-11-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131128133323/http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0%2C9171%2C838850%2C00.html |archivedate=2013-11-28 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。

来自[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]][[伯班克_(加利福尼亚州)|伯班克]]的14岁女孩卡拉·加里蒂（{{lang|en|Carla Garrity}}）认为科尔没有做出任何值得受此礼遇的功劳，因此对其全家得以参加新总统就职典礼表示反对。她在给自己国会选区[[联邦众议员|联邦众议员]][[埃德温·赖内克|埃德·赖内克]]（{{lang|en|Ed Reinecke}}）的信中写道，自己曾非常努力地为尼克松及其他共和党候选人工作，“因此，我非常反对一个俄亥俄州的13岁女孩只是举了块‘让我们团结起来’的牌子就获邀参加就职典礼。那牌子甚至都不是她写了，她连看都没看！”<ref name="Garrity 1968–11–17">{{citation | last = Garrity | first = Carla | date = 1968-11-17 | title = Letter to Congressman Ed Reinecke | work = Nixon Presidential Returned Materials Collection: White House Special Files (WHSF) Box 19, Folder 3 (Virtual Library) | publisher = Richard Nixon Presidential Library and Museum | archivedate = 2012-09-23 | deadurl = no | quote = Therefore, I am very much against that 13-year old girl in Ohio who held up the sign 'Bring us Together' being invited to the inaugural. She didn't even ''read'' or ''write'' it! | url = http://www.nixonlibrary.gov/virtuallibrary/documents/whsfreturned/WHSF_Box_19/WHSF19-03.pdf | format = PDF | accessdate = 2013-11-28 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120923220552/http://www.nixonlibrary.gov/virtuallibrary/documents/whsfreturned/WHSF_Box_19/WHSF19-03.pdf }}</ref>赖内克将这封信转交给了尼克松的助手[[约翰·埃利希曼|约翰·埃利希曼]]，并附有自己的评论：“我猜在尼克松竞选团体中工作的其他年轻人可能也会有卡拉这样的反应。”<ref name="Reinecke 1968–12–03">{{citation | last = Reinecke | first = Ed | date = 1968-12-03 | title = Memo to John Ehrlichman | work = Nixon Presidential Returned Materials Collection: White House Special Files (WHSF) | publisher = Richard Nixon Presidential Library and Museum | quote = I suspect that Carla's reaction may be shared by other young people who worked in the Nixon campaign | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120923220552/http://www.nixonlibrary.gov/virtuallibrary/documents/whsfreturned/WHSF_Box_19/WHSF19-03.pdf | archivedate = 2012-09-23 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.nixonlibrary.gov/virtuallibrary/documents/whsfreturned/WHSF_Box_19/WHSF19-03.pdf | format = PDF | accessdate = 2013-11-28 }}</ref>尼克松的另一位助手查尔斯·E·斯图尔特（{{lang|en|Charles E. Stuart}}）向赖内克回复道：“维奇·琳恩并不是因为她举起了那句标语或是因为制作了一句标语而被邀请参加就职典礼，而是因为事实证明她举起的这句标语给了尼克松先生一种鼓舞。”他还表示自己相信这一邀请会在其他拥护尼克松的年轻人中得到良好的回响<ref name="Stuart 1968–12–17">{{citation | last = Stuart | first = Charles E. | date = 1968-12-17 | title = Letter to Congressman Ed Reinecke | work = Nixon Presidential Returned Materials Collection: White House Special Files (WHSF) Box 19, Folder 3 (Virtual Library) | publisher = Richard Nixon Presidential Library and Museum | url = http://www.nixonlibrary.gov/virtuallibrary/documents/whsfreturned/WHSF_Box_19/WHSF19-03.pdf | format = PDF | quote = Vicki Lynne has been invited to the inauguration not because she carried the sign, or even because she made the sign, but rather because the sign which she did carry proved to be an inspiration to Mr. Nixon. | accessdate = 2013-11-28 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120923220552/http://www.nixonlibrary.gov/virtuallibrary/documents/whsfreturned/WHSF_Box_19/WHSF19-03.pdf | archivedate = 2012-09-23 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。

== 政治应用和余波 ==

[[File:Bring_Us_Together_video.ogv|left]]
[[File:Deshfire.jpg|thumb]]

尼克松就职典礼筹办委员会希望用“让我们团结起来”作为典礼的主题，不过萨菲尔表示：“那不是竞选的主题。”<ref name="Evans Novak 1971" />萨菲尔和其他总统助手认为，行政部门要做的应该是设法推进议程，而不是寻求对政策的共识<ref name="Safire 2007–09–02" />，而即将在新政府中担任[[白宫办公厅主任|白宫办公厅主任]]的[[H·R·霍尔德曼|H·R·霍尔德曼]]则得以将典礼主题改成了“一起前进”（{{lang|en|Forward Together}}）。不过讽刺的是，这句“让我们团结起来”之后经常被民主党国会议员用来反击尼克松及其行政部门，每次当提出的议题出现分歧时，民主党议员就会用这句话来进行攻击。此外，当[[莱昂·帕内塔|莱昂·帕内塔]]因在有关[[基本权_(宪法学)|公民权利]]政策的问题上反对[[白宫|白宫]]的“[[南方战略|南方战略]]”（{{lang|en|Southern strategy}}）而被解除职务后，他也用这句标语来作为其揭密文章的标题<ref name="Evans Novak 1971" />。据萨菲尔所说，使用这句号码来反对尼克松表明，一句可以激起情绪的口号既有利，也有弊<ref name="Safire 2008" />。

尼克松的顾问们一直否认总统有放弃让美国人民团结起来的目标<ref name="Sidey 1970">{{citation | last = Sidey | first = Hugh | date = 1970-05-15 | title = Nixon in a crisis of leadership | journal = Life | volume = 68 | pages = 28–29}}</ref>。然而，即使是这些人中也出现了分裂，他们中有一部分寻求国家团结，而另一部分，如尼克松的竞选经理兼职[[美国司法部长|司法部长]][[约翰·N·米切尔|约翰·N·米切尔]]则认为，尼克松应该把精力集中在维持那些投票支持自己的选民上，并且还要想办法赢得那些选择支持第三方候选人[[阿拉巴马州|阿拉巴马州]][[州长|州长]][[乔治·华莱士|乔治·华莱士]]的选民，来作为赢得[[1972年美国总统选举|1972年美国总统选举]]的关键<ref name="Drew 2007">{{citation | last = Drew | first = Elizabeth | year = 2007 | title = Richard M. Nixon | publisher = Macmillan | place = New York, N.Y. | isbn = 978-0-8050-6963-1 | url = http://books.google.com/?id=OLBC9xLD0zYC | accessdate = 2013-11-28 | pages = 35–36}}</ref>。据萨菲尔所说，尼克松上任后和他的顾问们决定，他还不需要让国家团结起来，而只需要通过呼吁那些不会敌视尼克松及其政策的选民來支持自己，以确保自己能在1972年选举中获胜，这些选民之后被称为[[沉默的大多数|沉默的大多数]]<ref name="Safire 2005 p308–310">{{citation | last = Safire | first = William | year = 2005 | title = Before the Fall: An Inside View of the pre-Watergate White House | publisher = Transaction Publishers | place = Piscataway, N.J. | isbn = 978-1-4128-0466-0 | url = http://books.google.com/?id=4yPRj_ZQNSYC&dq=Bring+Us+Together+Nixon | accessdate = 2013-11-28 | pages = 308–310}}</ref>。[[历史学家|历史学家]]斯坦利·库特勒（{{lang|en|Stanley Kutler}}）在自己有关尼克松政府的书中指出，尼克松的政府加大了美国的分裂程度，但整个国家最终还是在他任内团结了起来——反对尼克松并要求他下台<ref name="Kutler 1992">{{citation | last = Kutler | first = Stanley | year = 1992 | title = The wars of Watergate: the last crisis of Richard Nixon | publisher = W.W. Norton & Co | place = New York | isbn = 978-0-393-30827-3 | url = http://books.google.com/?id=k2U9w6RVpowC | accessdate = 2013-11-28 | pages = 10, 414}}</ref>。

1970年下半年，维奇·琳恩·科尔在一次接受采访时表示，尼克松已经尽了自己最大的努力<ref name="Bryan Times 1970–05–12">{{citation | periodical = The Bryan Times | date = 1970-05-12 | title = Vicki Cole keeps faith in President | url = http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=799&dat=19700512&id=OncJAAAAIBAJ&sjid=I0gDAAAAIBAJ&pg=4110,2509731 | accessdate = 2013-11-28 | archive-date = 2016-05-27 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160527031042/https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=799&dat=19700512&id=OncJAAAAIBAJ&sjid=I0gDAAAAIBAJ&pg=4110,2509731 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。1972年竞选期间，科尔担任俄亥俄州未来选民组织的主席，为尼克松的竞选作宣传。之后她远离了[[美国政治|政治]]，把自己的课余时间投入到马匹训练和表演上<ref name="LATimes 1977–01–17">{{citation | periodical = Los Angeles Times | date = 1977-01-17 | title = 'Bring-Us-Together' girl asks, 'Which way now?' | url = http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/offers.html?url=%2Flatimes%2Fdoc%2F158240350.html%3FFMT%3DAI%26FMTS%3DABS%3AAI%26type%3Dhistoric%26date%3DJan%252017%2C%25201977%26author%3D%26pub%3DLos%2520Angeles%2520Times%2520(1886-Current%2520File)%26edition%3D%26startpage%3D%26desc%3DBring-Us-Together%2520Girl%2520Asks%2520%27Which%2520Way%2520Now%3F%27 | accessdate = 2013-11-28 | archive-date = 2016-03-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160306211804/http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/offers.html?url=%2Flatimes%2Fdoc%2F158240350.html%3FFMT%3DAI%26FMTS%3DABS%3AAI%26type%3Dhistoric%26date%3DJan%252017%2C%25201977%26author%3D%26pub%3DLos%2520Angeles%2520Times%2520%281886-Current%2520File%29%26edition%3D%26startpage%3D%26desc%3DBring-Us-Together%2520Girl%2520Asks%2520%27Which%2520Way%2520Now%3F%27 | dead-url = no }}{{subscription required}}</ref>。1974年尼克松因[[水门事件|水门事件]]而辞职，科尔拒绝对之发表评论<ref name="Pittsburgh Post-Gazette 1974–08–09">{{citation | periodical = Pittsburgh Post-Gazette | date = 1974-08-09 | title = 'Forward Together' girl quiet on Nixon | url = http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=7wIOAAAAIBAJ&sjid=Vm0DAAAAIBAJ&pg=7134,981694 | accessdate = 2013-12-02 | archive-date = 2016-05-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160506171214/https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=7wIOAAAAIBAJ&sjid=Vm0DAAAAIBAJ&pg=7134,981694 | dead-url = no }}</ref>，但到了1977年，她在一次接受采访时表示自己虽然也认为尼克松应该辞职，但还是对他感到同情<ref name="LATimes 1977–01–17" />。

萨菲尔在自己2008年出版的政治辞典中回忆起这段往事时写道，尼克松的第一次就职典礼过去几年后，他有一次问起摩尔，对方究竟是在什么地方看到科尔举着那块标语，还是这都只是他的想像，以为自己看到了一些实际上不存在的东西<ref name="Safire 2008" />。萨菲尔在2009年逝世前最后几年所写的专栏文章中认为，这个标语“几乎好到让人不敢相信”<ref name="Safire 2008–01–20">{{citation | last = Safire | first = William | date = 2008-01-20 | periodical = The New York Times | title = On Language ("Fired Up") | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/20/magazine/20wwln-safire-t.html?scp=2&sq=bring+us+together+safire&st=nyt&_r=0 | accessdate = 2013-11-28 | archive-date = 2013-12-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20131220092741/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/20/magazine/20wwln-safire-t.html?scp=2&sq=bring+us+together+safire&st=nyt&_r=0 | dead-url = no }}</ref>，觉得有可能都是摩尔“编出来的”<ref name="Safire 2007–09–02" />。
